In[6]:
# Fill missing children values with 0
df['children'] = df['children'].fillna(0)

# Fill missing country values
df['country'] = df['country'].fillna('Unknown')

# Remove rows with negative ADR (invalid prices)
df = df[df['adr'] >= 0]

# Remove duplicate rows
df = df.drop_duplicates()

# Total nights stayed

# Total number of guests

In[16]:
# Correct calendar order for months
month_order = [
    'January','February','March','April','May','June',
    'July','August','September','October','November','December'
]

df_nc = df_nc.copy()

df_nc.loc[:, 'arrival_date_month'] = pd.Categorical(
    df_nc['arrival_date_month'],
    categories=month_order,
    ordered=True
)
In[18]:
monthly_adr = (
    df_nc
    .groupby(['arrival_date_month', 'hotel'], observed=True)['adr']
    .mean()
    .reset_index()
)
monthly_adr.head()
Out[18]:

0 January City Hotel 83.180097
1 January Resort Hotel 48.542066

In[19]:
plt.figure(figsize=(12,6))
sns.lineplot(
    data=monthly_adr,
    x='arrival_date_month',
    y='adr',
    hue='hotel',
    marker='o'
)
plt.title("Monthly Average ADR by Hotel Type")
plt.xlabel("Month")
plt.ylabel("Average Daily Rate (ADR)")
plt.xticks(rotation=45)
plt.show()

Insight: ADR shows strong seasonality. Resort Hotels experience peak prices during summer months, while City Hotels show more stable pricing throughout the year.

In[20]:
plt.figure(figsize=(8,5))
sns.countplot(x='meal', hue='hotel', data=df_nc)
plt.title("Meal Preferences by Hotel Type")
plt.xlabel("Meal Type")
plt.ylabel("Number of Bookings")
plt.show()

Insight: Meal preferences differ between City and Resort hotels. Bed & Breakfast (BB) is the most common meal type, while Resort Hotels show relatively higher preference for full board and half board options.

In[30]:
cancel_by_month = (
    df
    .groupby(['arrival_date_month', 'hotel'], observed=True)['is_canceled']
    .mean()
    .reset_index()
)

plt.figure(figsize=(12,6))
sns.lineplot(
    data=cancel_by_month,
    x='arrival_date_month',
    y='is_canceled',
    hue='hotel',
    marker='o'
)
plt.title("Monthly Cancellation Rate by Hotel Type")
plt.xlabel("Month")
plt.ylabel("Cancellation Rate")
plt.xticks(rotation=45)
plt.show()

Insight: City Hotels have a higher cancellation rate compared to Resort Hotels. Cancellations also vary by season, with certain peak months experiencing significantly higher cancellation volumes.
